    <string name="slide1_title">Easier Communication for Autistic Children</string>
    <string name="slide1_desc">
        Feelings makes communication between your child and you easier.\n\n
        When your child has a tough time expressing his feelings,
        he may select an emoji representing his emotion on Feelings,
        and a text will be sent to you or anyone in Feelings\' contact list.
    </string>

    <string name="slide2_title">How To Use</string>
    <string name="slide2_desc">
        \tTo set up the app for your child, firstly choose a password for the app.
         This is to prevent the child from accessing the Settings and manipulating the app\'s data.\n
        \tSecondly, select the contacts you wish the texts to be sent to.
        You may select up to 5 different contacts.\n
        \tThen Feelings will be ready to be used by your child. You may change password or contacts in the Setting if you need to.\n
    </string>

